# Normalize line endings across every clone.
#
# The repo is developed on WSL/Linux (LF). Without this file, a Windows checkout gets CRLF working
# copies, so git reports ~every file as "modified" and blocks `git pull` / `git checkout`. Forcing
# LF in BOTH the index and the working tree (eol=lf) makes clones byte-identical on every OS.
# `text=auto` still auto-detects binaries so an undeclared binary is never corrupted.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts must be LF to run (redundant with the above, but explicit + intent-revealing).
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.mjs   text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply text/eol conversion.
*.pptx  binary
*.potx  binary
*.gguf  binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.webp  binary
*.ico   binary
*.icns  binary
*.pdf   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
